(2273, NULL, 'groupadministration.title', 'User groups', 1),
(2274, NULL, 'help.page.gamemodelmetadata', '<h3>Specification of a game model</h3>\n<p>A game model consists of:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>metadata &ndash; the descriptive information of a game i.e. the information as it is given in a game catalogue.</li>\n    <li>status &ndash; a game model that is not yet finished automatically gets the status &ldquo;Under construction&rdquo;. You complete it by giving it the status &ldquo;Personal&rdquo; or you hand it over by giving it the status &ldquo;Public&rdquo;.</li>\n    <li>roles &ndash; the names of the roles: it is best to choose functional names, e.g. seller or alderman; at the construction of a game manifest a role is linked to the playground object (the motor shop, the town hall); when creating a game session a role is given to one or more participants.</li>\n    <li>steps-of-play &ndash; the names of the steps-of-play (also called phases, levels, stages).</li>\n    <li>activities &ndash; the activities that are offered to a certain role in a certain step- of-play in the game; this can concern an individual activity that leads to the uploading of a file, a social activity that leads to the sending of a message to another role or a progress&nbsp;activity that leads the game session to another step-of-play.</li>\n    <li>activities schedule &ndash; a matrix of roles and steps-of-play; every cell indicates which activities will be offered to that role at that step-of-play.</li>\n    <li>resources &ndash; files that can be offered to participants as resource materials during one or more activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When you give a game model the status &ldquo;Personal&rdquo;, you can include it in a game manifest and then have game sessions. As long as they are active you can view and copy the game model, but not edit it. You can also give your game model the status &ldquo;Public&rdquo;. Then you hand it over to the publisher who can give it to third parties or let them use it under certain conditions.</p>', 1),
(2275, NULL, 'shift.left', 'Shift left', 1),
(2276, NULL, 'help.page.session', '<h3>Home Page</h3>\n<p>This page enables you to participate in a certain active game session from a role that is appointed to you. If the session is ended you can view the end situation. At the left side, you find the status of the current session and a menu. Each of the menu options leads you to a sub-page. All the sub-pages have the same menu and can bring you back to this Home Page. At the right side, you find an overview of recent messages, activities and uploaded files.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The menu options are:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>Current situation</b> &ndash; the name of the game session, current status (Running, Finished, Aborted), your role and the current step-of-play.</li>\n    <li><b>Home Page</b> &ndash; hyperlink to go back to the Homepage of this game session.</li>\n    <li><b>Messages</b> &ndash; hyperlink to the Messages sub-page with an overview of the received and sent messages, the possibility to send a new message, to delete a message, to view the deleted messages and if necessary to put them back.</li>\n    <li><b>Activities</b> &ndash; hyperlink to the Activities&nbsp;sub-page that lists the activities of the current step-of-play and the current role, gives the possibility to read and execute them.</li>\n    <li><b>Playground</b> &ndash; hyperlink to open a new window that gives access to the map, the directory and objects and the background information on the playground. It is possible that more than one playground is connected to your session.</li>\n    <li><b>Game Intro</b> &ndash; hyperlink to a sub-page with a description of the used game model.</li>\n    <li><b>Colophon</b> &ndash; hyperlink to a description of the current game session.</li>\n    <li><b>Contacts</b> &ndash; a list of the roles from the current game session plus the Cyberdam object that role is connected with; clicking on one of these contacts shows the playground object page from the playground directory.</li>\n</ul>', 1),
(2277, NULL, 'help.page.gamemodelstepsofplay', '<h3>Steps-of-play</h3>\n<p>On this page you can enter the names of the steps-of-play of the game model. The order you choose you will find when filling out the activities schedule. steps-of-play are also called phases, levels, stages or stadia.</p>', 1),
