(2307, NULL, 'help.page.playgroundobjecteditor', '<h3>Specification of a playground object</h3>\n<p>A playground object consists of:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>URI</b> &ndash; a unique code for the object (e.g. sd- 101) that the editors of a playground agree on among themselves.</li>\n    <li><b>Name</b> -&nbsp;name of the object as it is seen on the map and in the directory.</li>\n    <li><b>Caption</b> &ndash; the text that appears in the popup screen on the map.</li>\n    <li><b>Category</b> - the type of object that leads to a particular colour of the mark on the map.</li>\n    <li><b>Miniature</b> - a small image that appears in the popup screen on the map.</li>\n    <li><b>Image</b> - the image that is covered in the directory.</li>\n    <li><b>Horizontally and vertically</b> - coordinates of the position on the map; 0,0 is the top-left corner of the map; 1000,1000 is the bottom-right corner.</li>\n    <li><b>Map and directory</b> &ndash; selecting means that the object is visible on the map, respectively directory (under the condition that the status is &quot;Public&quot;).</li>\n    <li><b>Status</b> - the status of the object can be: &quot;Under construction&quot;, &quot;Public&quot; and &quot;Out of order&quot;; when the status is &quot;Public&quot;, the object can be visible on the map and/or the directory.</li>\n</ul>', 1),
