(2357, NULL, 'help.page.sendmessage', '<h3>New message</h3>\n<p>This form enables you to create and send a new message. Select and de-select receivers and/or attachments by CTRL-mouseclick.</p>\n<p>You can create and send a new message to one or more roles from the current game session. You can make a lay out for the text of the message. You can only include images in the message through a URL link. You can send attachments with your message. For that you can choose from previously uploaded files. If the attachment you want to send is not there, you have to upload it first and then create and send your message plus attachment.</p>', 1),
(2358, NULL, 'variableedit.title', 'Edit variable', 1),
(2359, NULL, 'help.page.gamemodelactivityedit', '<h3>Activity</h3>\n<p>An activity specification consists of:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>name</b> &ndash; a description of the activity of only a few words, as it will appear on the screens of the participants of the game session.</li>\n    <li><b>explanation</b> &ndash; a more elaborate explanation of the activity for the participants.</li>\n    <li><b>resources </b>&ndash; documents that are offered to the participants as resources to the activity; these documents are part of the game model.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A message&nbsp;activity specification also contains:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>addressees</b> &ndash; with a message activity you can mark the roles for whom the message is intended.</li>\n    <li><b>standard</b> text &ndash; with a message activity you can mark a standard text for the message you want to send.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A progress activity specification also contains:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>options</b> &ndash; you can mark one out of max. 15 options and the steps- of-play that need to follow those options.</li>\n</ul>', 1),
(2360, NULL, 'help.page.playgroundeditorpage', '<h3>Playground</h3>\n<p>Use this form to specify a playground, the playground objects excluded.</p>\n<p>The form contains:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Playground-name - the name of the playgfround as shown to the participants of game sessions.</li>\n    <li>Caption - a caption text that will be shown to the participants as well.</li>\n    <li>URI - a unique code for the playground.</li>\n    <li>Description - background information about this playground; this information will be shown to participants of game sessions.</li>\n    <li>Version - a version identifier, e.g. the language of the playground.</li>\n    <li>Map - a reference to a map (the name of a Flash-file on the Cyberdam server or the URL of an external map.</li>\n    <li>Status - the status of the playground; options: &quot;under construction&quot;, &quot;public&quot;, and &quot;out of order&quot;. When the status = &quot;Public&quot;, the playground can be used in game manifests.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1),
