(2456, NULL, 'help.page.swfupload', '<h3>More information needed?</h3> <p>Send an e-mail to <a href="mailto:helpdesk@cyberdam.nl">helpdesk@cyberdam.nl</a>&nbsp;referring to the title of your screen page and ask for it!</p>', 1),
(2457, NULL, 'help.page.gamemodelvariables', '<p>Cyberdam uses variables. These are memory positions that have a name and to which content (values) may be allocated. Cyberdam has variables on three levels: system, game model and role. Some variables have been predefined, other ones can be specified by the users. The game model author determines the variables at model and at role level. The game author specifies the variables at game model and role level. The predefined values are:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>model.name (the name of the game.model)</li>\n    <li>model.caption (the caption of the game model</li>\n    <li>role.name (the name of the&nbsp; role)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When a user specifies a new variable, they can either alloate an initial value or not.</p>\n<p>A game model author can incorporate the value of variables in a range of texts, e.g. the desription texts of activities.&nbsp;Names of variables placed between &quot;[&quot; and &quot;]&quot;'' ] are replaced bytheir values.</p>\n<p>When a game author adds form activities to their model, the users are enabled to change certain valies during their session.</p>', 1),
