(2509, NULL, 'help.page.creategamesession', '<h3>New game session</h3>\n<p>With this form, you can create a new game session and manage an existing one.</p>\n<p>A &nbsp;game session consists of:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li>name - the name of the game session; you choose the name of the game model in combination with a reference of the user group and/or the period in which the game session occurs; keep the name short and clear; it appears as title on the concerning participants&rsquo; pages.</li>\n    <li>game manifest &ndash; the name of the used game manifest; be aware: once you have chosen this it can not be changed for reasons of consistency; if necessary delete the game manifest and create a new one.</li>\n    <li>roles participants &ndash; as soon as you have chosen a game manifest the roles will automatically appear on screen, with your own name behind every role as the participant who will play that role; if you wish to execute a test run this means you are done with the role appointing; if this is not the case you can delete your own name and add one or more other names per role.</li>\n    <li>status &ndash; as soon as you start a game session it has the status &ldquo;Being prepared&rdquo;; is your role appointing completed, you can give the game session the status &ldquo;Ready-to-Run&rdquo;; if you wish to change anything, you have to go back to the status &ldquo;Being Prepared&rdquo;; you start the game session by giving it the status Running.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Notice that more participants can play a certain role together. It is also possible for one participant to play several roles.</p>', 1),
