(2700, NULL, 'help.page.languagepackimport', '<h3>Import language pack</h3>\n<p>You only can import language packs in Cyberdam, that have been exported by a Cyberdam system as well. A language pack namely is a zepped XML-file with a specific structure. When Cyberdam exports such a file, the structure is valid from the start. It would be very inconvenient to compose such a file in a correct way.</p>\n<p>Importing a language pack is a matter of &quot;a;; or nothing&quot;. You only can replace an existing lanuage pack in total, not partially.</p>', 1),
