(2727, NULL, 'help.page.gamemaster', '<h3>Game-sessions (management)</h3>\n<p>Game Masters start and manage game sessions. They choose a game manifest, connect one or more participants to every role and let the game session begin. Then they can manage the game session. They can view (and use) the homepage of every role in the game session; they can also edit the role appointment and if necessary end the game session.</p>\n<p>On this page you will find a list of game sessions. You can view, edit delete and copy existing game sessions. You can also create a new game session. A game session can have the following statuses: Being prepared,&nbsp; Ready-to-Run, Running, Finished (normal ending), Aborted (abnormal ending), Cancelled (never started). If you wish to start multiple parallel game sessions, you first start a new game session and copy it as often as needed. You then complete the role dedication in every game session and start every game session separately.</p>\n<p>Send an e-mail to <a href="mailto:helpdesk@cyberdam.nl">helpdesk@cyberdam.nl</a>&nbsp;referring to the title of your screen page and ask for it!</p>', 1),
