(2827, NULL, 'help.page.variable', '<p>Cyberdam uses variables. These are memory locations that have a name and may contain data (a value).</p>\n<p>Cyberdam has three levels of variables: system, game model and role. At system level one default variable exists: system.datetime. Its value is the actual date plus time. The system manager can define other system variables and give them an initial value or not.</p>\n<p>A game odel author can include the actual value of a variable in a variety of texts, e.g. the description of activities. A game model author also can add so-called form activities to game models. These give participants to game sessions the opportunity to change certain values during the sessions.</p>', 1),
(2828, NULL, 'help.page.playgrounddirectory', '<h3>Playground directory</h3>\n<p>This page contains the directory of Cyberdam. You can select this directory on name, category, caption and address, from either side. When you select the name of an object, you will go to a page with more detailed information on that object.</p>', 1),
