(2921, NULL, 'help.page.gamemanifestcomposer', '<h3>Game manifests</h3>\n<p>Game manifest composers dictate the relation between game model and playground. They connect a game model to a certain playground and indicate which role is connected to which playground object.</p>\n<p>On this page you find a list of game manifests. You can view, edit delete and copy existing game manifests. You can also add a new game manifest. When you give a game manifest the status &quot;Personal&quot;, you can have a game session. You can also give your game manifest the status &quot;Public&quot;. Then you hand it over to a publisher, who gives it to a third party or lets them use it under certain conditions.</p>', 1),
