(2940, NULL, 'help.page.playground', '<h3>Playground map</h3>\n<p>The options a playground map has to offer may vary. Some maps are static pictures, other maps are interactive modules. One of the latter is the interactive city map of Cyberdam. It offers the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n    <li><b>Navigator</b> - opening a popup screen with a little overview chart and a marker.</li>\n    <li><b>Legend</b> &ndash; opening a popup screen with the explanation of the colours of the map symbols.</li>\n    <li><b>Scrolling</b> &ndash; with the arrow symbols in the four corners of the map screen or by dragging the mouse over the chart.</li>\n    <li><b>Zooming in/zooming out</b> &ndash; You can zoom in with the Plus-magnifying glass, the &quot;A&quot; key or the numerical &quot;+&quot; key; you can zoom out with he Minus- magnifying glass, the &quot;Z&quot; key or the numerical &quot;- &quot; key.</li>\n    <li><b>Selecting</b> &ndash; When you select a pictogram on the map, the popup screen opens with a short description and a link to the description of the concerning object in the directory.</li>\n</ul>', 1),
