(3818, NULL, 'homepage.releasenotes', '<h3>Release notes Cyberdam 2.3 build 20110207 (implemented on this server on 14 May 2011)</h3>\r\n<h4>Changes</h4>\r\n<p><span>Most changes have to do with minor improvements in usability and the fixing of some bugs. The major issues are:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span>In a game model that was already used in a game manifest, the game author could freely change almost anything. From now, at least the number of roles is fixed.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span>In the case that two participants were playing the same role and each of them was executing the same activity, both could bring this activity to a normal end. From now, the participant who is the first one to complete the activity is treated in the regular way. The other participant receives </span>an error message like &quot;activity no longer available&quot; upon completion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Extra</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The right part of a session home page consists of a HUD (Heads-Up Display, possibly empty) plus most recent incoming messages, activties and uploads. From now the game author can choose between either this &quot;classic&quot; session home page or a session home page with a Heads-Up Display only.</li>\r\n    <li>During a certain step-of-play a role could execute each activity only once. By adding the text cyberdam.makeActivityAvailable() to the activity script, the game author can indicate that the role may execute that activity once again (and again).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Press Backspace to continue.</h3>', 1),
